{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"57ba7e48-b40e-4563-9f77-7fb025807255","content":"`.testsettings` is a legacy format — modern MSTest (v3+) ignores it. You need to migrate to a **`.runsettings`** file. Here's the equivalent for your three settings:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout` property | `<TestTimeout>` in `<MSTest>` |\n| Assembly resolution / deployment | `<DeploymentEnabled>` in `<MSTest>` |\n| Code coverage data collector | `<DataCollector>` in `<DataCollectionRunSettings>` |","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01JZuAqWcsDRnw46jerHJeoo","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating runsettings migration"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01KJt7Hy5ZWhFZ2Cntw38UFo","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-cdfa4ed9f764434bbb53eeaea9a7f4eb/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <!-- Replaces TestTimeout property (value in milliseconds) -->\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n    <!-- Replaces AssemblyResolution / TestDirectory deployment -->\n    <DeploymentEnabled>true</DeploymentEnabled>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://Microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.CoverageCollectorDataCollector, Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector, Culture=neutral\">\n        <Configuration>\n          <CodeCoverage />\n        </Configuration>\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-cdfa4ed9f764434bbb53eeaea9a7f4eb/local.runsettings."}],"interactionId":"73d4a731-8a9d-41a2-8b3a-885f17257b82","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file with:\n1. Assembly resolution / test deployment set